Firefighters and police were seen outside the office of Mike Freer MP

Police are investigating a suspected arson attack at the office of North London Conservative MP Mike Freer.

A fire broke out at the rear of the North Finchley and Golders Green MP's constituency office at around 19:00 on Christmas Eve.

The Met Police confirmed it is investigating the fire.

Mr Freer told the BBC the fire happened at the rear of the premises and no one was in the building at the time of the incident.

He continued: "The police and fire brigade were on the scene in minutes and have been incredible in their response."

London Fire Brigade (LFB) confirmed the fire started in a shed outside the office before spreading to the rest of the building.

An LFB spokesperson said: "An external shed was destroyed by fire. Part of the first, second and third floors of the property were also damaged by the blaze."

In a statement, a Metropolitan Police spokesperson said: "The cause of the fire is under investigation as it is believed it may have been started deliberately. There have been no arrests."

Pictures posted on social media showed Metropolitan Police and LFB vehicles at the premises on Sunday evening.

Mr Freer has represented the North London constituency since 2010.

He is parliamentary under-secretary of state for courts and legal services, a junior role in the Ministry of Justice.

#technicalskillsdevelopment:
Stay updated with the latest technologies and tools in your industry. Consider taking online courses, attending workshops, or earning certifications to enhance your technical skillsset.

#continuouslearning:
Make learning a daily habit. Set aside time each day to read industry blogs, listen to podcasts, or watch educational videos. Use apps like Duolingo or Coursera to expand your knowledge in various areas.

#lifelonglearning:
Embrace the idea that learning doesn't stop once you graduate or leave a job. Seek out opportunities to learn new skills and gain new knowledge throughout your entire career.

#continuededucation:
Consider pursuing a degree or advanced certification to further your education and increase your marketability in your industry.

#skillshaping:
Identify the skills you need to succeed in your current or desired role and develop a plan to acquire them. Set specific, measurable goals and track your progress.

#skillbuilding:
Focus on building your core competencies and mastering the skills that are most valuable in your industry. Use resources like LinkedIn Learning, Skillshare, or Udemy to learn new skills.

#professionaldevelopmentplan:
Create a personalized professional development plan to guide your career growth. Set specific, measurable goals and establish a timeline for achieving them.

#personalbrandingstrategies:
Develop a strong personal brand that sets you apart from your competition. Use social media, networking events, and other channels to build your professional reputation and establish thought leadership in your industry.

#jobinterviewpreparation:
Prepare thoroughly for job interviews by researching the company, practicing common interview questions, and preparing examples of your past achievements.

#careercoaching:
Consider working with a career coach to help you identify your strengths and weaknesses, develop a career strategy, and navigate job transitions.

#careergrowthmindset:
Adopt a growth mindset that embraces challenges and sees failures as opportunities for learning. Focus on developing your skills and knowledge, rather than just achieving specific outcomes.

#careerworklifebalance:
Find a balance between your professional and personal life to ensure long-term career success and happiness. Prioritize self-care, set boundaries, and make time for hobbies and relationships.

#mentorshipping:
Seek out mentors or coaches who can provide guidance, support, and advice as you navigate your career. Offer to mentor others in return to build your professional network and expand your knowledge.

#apprenticeships:
Consider apprenticeships or other forms of on-the-job training to gain practical experience and develop new skills. Many industries offer apprenticeships, and they can be a great way to gain valuable experience while earning a salary.

#internships:
Apply for internships to gain practical experience, build your professional network, and learn new skills. Internships can also be a great way to explore different career paths and industries.
